            "answer_text": "No. You need a comma after the word \u201crequest\u201d and a period after \u201cconsideration.\u201d The sentence is also cumbersome. How about \u201cI attached the details you requested\u201d? Keep it simple. Avoid \u201cas per your request.\u201d Always. There is never a situation where that phrase is the best way to let your correspondent know you\u2019re responding to their request. That phrase is wordy and makes the user sound pretentious, almost legalistic. ",
